# Day 16-17 Scratch &mdash; AND OR and Randomness

First, let's explore the tenth lesson in the unit. To begin, find your ECS Version 5 curriculum and open to page 167-169.

[Access a Digital Copy of the lesson>>](http://code.org/ecs#page=167)

## Key Concepts

- Students will use conditionals with the "and" block, "or" block and "pick random\_to\_" block to write a grade program and a dice program.

## Common Difficulties

This lesson introduces the "and" block,  "or" block and "random" block. It might be helpful to do an unplugged activity to help students grasp the concept of And/Or.  Truth tables can also be a helpful way to teach more complicated conditionals.

